stimulus.content:
A programmer writes a function that is supposed to check if a number is positive. He writes:

IF(number > 0)
{
    DISPLAY("negative")
}
ELSE
{
    DISPLAY("positive")
}

A code comment reads:
// Multiply length by width to get area
// Returns: area as a number

The code below performs the multiplication and returns the result.

A programmer writes:

IF(temperature > 32)
{
    DISPLAY("Below freezing")
}
ELSE
{
    DISPLAY("Above freezing")
}

He intended: display 'Below freezing' when temperature is BELOW 32.
